Got it, girls?

551
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:31,932
Yes.

552
00:33:31,933 --> 00:33:35,660
That's why nothing's working out for me.

553
00:33:39,133 --> 00:33:40,599
What?

554
00:33:40,599 --> 00:33:41,467
What's up with him?

555
00:33:41,468 --> 00:33:44,832
He might lose his apartment.

556
00:33:44,832 --> 00:33:46,220
What do you mean?

557
00:33:46,220 --> 00:33:50,980

558
00:33:50,980 --> 00:33:53,570
I'm going crazy.

559
00:33:55,066 --> 00:33:57,900
You still haven't gotten the money?

560
00:33:58,634 --> 00:34:02,465
I can't believe you couldn't get a loan because of low credit.

561
00:34:02,465 --> 00:34:04,600
What do I do?

562
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:08,400
It was my last hope in my miserable life.

563
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,865
Fate is so cruel.

564
00:34:09,866 --> 00:34:12,500
How can it give and snatch away at once?

565
00:34:12,500 --> 00:34:17,100
I don't want to lose it.

566
00:34:17,100 --> 00:34:18,799
Chief Editor, do you have any money...?

567
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:20,632
Where would I get ₩50 million?

568
00:34:20,633 --> 00:34:23,265
I'm scared to even spend ₩5,000 with my wife hawk-eyeing me.

569
00:34:23,266 --> 00:34:24,398
Right?

570
00:34:24,399 --> 00:34:26,380
I'm sorry.

571
00:34:28,333 --> 00:34:32,232
Come on. Why don't you ask Editor Yeo?

572
00:34:32,232 --> 00:34:34,165
Her lease was changed to a monthly rent.

573
00:34:34,165 --> 00:34:36,165
She got her deposit back.

574
00:34:36,165 --> 00:34:37,732
How can I ask Editor Yeo?

575
00:34:37,733 --> 00:34:38,667
I have a conscience.

576
00:34:38,667 --> 00:34:41,165
Just beg for forgiveness, you fool.

577
00:34:41,166 --> 00:34:42,499
You can't afford not to.

578
00:34:42,499 --> 00:34:43,898
No, I can't.

579
00:34:43,899 --> 00:34:46,200
If I ask her for money,

580
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:49,167
I won't be able to face her for the rest of my life.

581
00:34:55,099 --> 00:34:57,365
 At least he has a sense of decency.

582
00:34:57,366 --> 00:35:00,332
 How would he dare to ask me?

583
00:35:00,332 --> 00:35:03,899
So I'm going to interview architect Yoo Ji Sun.

584
00:35:03,899 --> 00:35:08,060
I'll show you the title and concept.

585
00:35:08,910 --> 00:35:12,380

586
00:35:12,380 --> 00:35:14,530

587
00:35:14,530 --> 00:35:16,099
What's wrong?

588
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:18,231
I'm sorry. I made a typo.

589
00:35:18,232 --> 00:35:19,931
What? A typo?

590
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:21,110
Oh, there...

591
00:35:21,110 --> 00:35:22,370

592
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:24,330

593
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:30,880
I think I saw it wrong.

594
00:35:34,399 --> 00:35:36,064
I'm sorry to interrupt your meeting.

595
00:35:36,065 --> 00:35:41,160
We're getting lunch. Pick a dish.

596
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:44,030

597
00:35:44,030 --> 00:35:45,633
What's wrong?

598
00:35:45,633 --> 00:35:47,333
What?

599
00:35:47,333 --> 00:35:49,230
Nothing.

600
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:50,180

601
00:35:50,180 --> 00:35:52,960

602
00:35:53,767 --> 00:35:56,666
What do you want? Did you choose?

603
00:35:56,666 --> 00:35:58,167
Young Won.

604
00:35:58,167 --> 00:36:00,033
Hey!

605
00:36:00,033 --> 00:36:01,431
Right.

606
00:36:01,431 --> 00:36:02,931
I don't want anything.

607
00:36:02,931 --> 00:36:05,270
I need to use the restroom.

608
00:36:08,967 --> 00:36:12,033
I told her to live a new life.

609
00:36:12,033 --> 00:36:15,470
But she's totally lost it.

610
00:36:19,466 --> 00:36:22,633
This is Editor Nam's storyboard.

611
00:36:22,633 --> 00:36:24,580
Wait.

612
00:36:25,866 --> 00:36:27,367
- Mi Ra is dying with joy, right? 
 - What?

613
00:36:27,367 --> 00:36:29,366
She didn't say anything?

614
00:36:30,465 --> 00:36:33,033
She must not have seen the lunch box yet.

615
00:36:33,033 --> 00:36:35,466
If she had, she'd be boasting to you.

616
00:36:35,467 --> 00:36:36,967
What?

617
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:40,665
 You broke down the solid wall called Jang Chan.

618
00:36:40,666 --> 00:36:43,200
 Mi Ra, you win.

619
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:47,090
 Let's officially go on a date.

620
00:36:49,767 --> 00:36:51,531
The heart is a funny thing.

621
00:36:51,532 --> 00:36:54,132
When someone keeps saying they like you,

622
00:36:54,133 --> 00:36:55,832
you eventually open your heart.

623
00:36:55,833 --> 00:36:57,367
- Close it. 
 - What?

624
00:36:57,367 --> 00:37:00,666
Close your heart.

625
00:37:00,666 --> 00:37:03,966
Mi Ra doesn't like you.

626
00:37:03,967 --> 00:37:06,132
What nonsense is that...?

627
00:37:06,133 --> 00:37:08,633
It's not nonsense.

628
00:37:08,633 --> 00:37:10,133
What?

629
00:37:10,133 --> 00:37:12,100
Then who...?

630
00:37:14,366 --> 00:37:17,340
 Attractive dimples.

631
00:37:35,566 --> 00:37:37,900
No!

632
00:37:37,900 --> 00:37:40,630
Mi Ra!

633
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:49,166
What's wrong?

634
00:37:49,166 --> 00:37:51,499
I thought I put in your favorite chocolate,

635
00:37:51,499 --> 00:37:52,532
but I forgot.

636
00:37:52,532 --> 00:37:53,999
Give it here. I'll put it in and give it back.

637
00:37:53,999 --> 00:37:55,332
No, it's okay.

638
00:37:55,333 --> 00:37:57,790
I said I'll put chocolate in!

639
00:38:04,733 --> 00:38:08,665
You know, Jang Chan is a strange person.

640
00:38:08,665 --> 00:38:09,566
No.

641
00:38:09,567 --> 00:38:12,620
Let's just say he's a sad person.

642
00:38:24,032 --> 00:38:25,833
I'm sorry.

643
00:38:47,633 --> 00:38:50,232
Oh, wait up!

644
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:12,432
23% of ₩50 million is...

645
00:39:12,432 --> 00:39:14,531
The interest alone is ₩12 million!

646
00:39:14,532 --> 00:39:16,740
This is insane.

647
00:39:18,366 --> 00:39:19,699
Oh, whatever.

648
00:39:19,699 --> 00:39:21,865
There's no other way.

649
00:39:22,733 --> 00:39:23,832
What?

650
00:39:23,833 --> 00:39:25,533
What's this?

651
00:39:29,433 --> 00:39:31,266
Settle the middle payment with that.

652
00:39:31,266 --> 00:39:32,766
Wait.

653
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:35,933
Why all of a sudden?

654
00:39:35,933 --> 00:39:38,064
What use is that question?

655
00:39:38,065 --> 00:39:39,432
Pay me back.

656
00:39:39,433 --> 00:39:41,500
With interest.

657
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:42,232
Forget it.

658
00:39:42,233 --> 00:39:43,898
How can I ask you for money?

659
00:39:43,899 --> 00:39:45,232
Don't want it? Then give it back.

660
00:39:45,232 --> 00:39:47,466
No, no, no.

661
00:39:47,466 --> 00:39:49,000
Seriously.

662
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:51,466
Thank you, Ui Joo.

663
00:39:51,466 --> 00:39:55,998
I won't ever forget your kindness.

664
00:39:57,801 --> 00:39:59,466
What would you do without me?

665
00:39:59,467 --> 00:40:02,699
- You, Nam Sang Soon! 
 - Ouch, ouch!

666
00:40:04,666 --> 00:40:06,434
I'm leaving.

667
00:40:06,434 --> 00:40:08,200
Hello?

668
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:09,632
Yes.

669
00:40:11,366 --> 00:40:13,200
It hurts.

670
00:40:27,666 --> 00:40:29,064
 What are you doing?

671
00:40:29,065 --> 00:40:31,198
 I distinctly told you to never do this again!

672
00:40:31,199 --> 00:40:34,332
 I just don't understand. I just can't.

673
00:40:34,333 --> 00:40:36,832
 Can you please just understand now?

674
00:40:36,833 --> 00:40:39,064
 Doesn't it affect you at all?

675
00:40:39,065 --> 00:40:41,166
 Am I the only one hurting?

676
00:40:41,166 --> 00:40:42,266
 Yes.

677
00:40:42,267 --> 00:40:45,432
 It doesn't affect me. I'm not hurting one bit.

678
00:40:45,432 --> 00:40:47,064
 So leave right now.

679
00:40:47,065 --> 00:40:48,665
 No.

680
00:40:48,665 --> 00:40:50,333
 I can't.

681
00:40:50,333 --> 00:40:52,000
 What?

682
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,967
 I'm not here because I want to be.

683
00:40:53,967 --> 00:40:56,499
 - You called me here. 
 -  What?

684
00:40:56,499 --> 00:40:58,899
 This is a dream. Your dream.

685
00:40:58,899 --> 00:41:02,367
 You're shamelessly dreaming about me!

686
00:41:04,366 --> 00:41:05,865
Yoo Ja Sung.

687
00:41:05,866 --> 00:41:07,966
What are you doing?

688
00:41:52,699 --> 00:41:55,800
A home is a vessel in which we place our life?

689
00:41:56,566 --> 00:41:59,866
My life is a total disaster.

690
00:42:02,899 --> 00:42:05,066
What time is it?

691
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:09,566
Where's my phone?

692
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:16,099
 My boyfrnd dumped me.

693
00:42:16,100 --> 00:42:19,165
 I wanna forgt him, but I caaaant.

694
00:42:19,165 --> 00:42:20,732
 What do I do?

695
00:42:20,733 --> 00:42:24,432
I must've written it while I was drunk.

696
00:42:25,399 --> 00:42:28,366
I should just hang myself.

697
00:42:31,500 --> 00:42:34,467
Oh? Sunbae?

698
00:42:37,633 --> 00:42:40,499
I was talking to Photographer Shin about work,

699
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:42,799
and learned he's going to the countryside by himself.

700
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:45,398
So I asked him to include us.

701
00:42:45,399 --> 00:42:49,265
Can you take me back? I want to stay home.

702
00:42:49,265 --> 00:42:50,832
You're spoiling the mood.

703
00:42:50,833 --> 00:42:55,132
It could look weird if it's just me and him.

704
00:42:55,133 --> 00:42:59,198
I want to get some fresh air, so be quiet and come along.

705
00:42:59,198 --> 00:43:01,999
Yes. Since we're out, let's have fun.

706
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,332
Yes!

707
00:43:03,333 --> 00:43:05,299
Let's stop by a service station.

708
00:43:05,300 --> 00:43:08,198
Young Won loves the braised potatoes sold there.

709
00:43:08,199 --> 00:43:09,867
Right, Young Won?

710
00:43:09,867 --> 00:43:11,334
Yes.

711
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:22,231
I have to hear my wife's nagging at home.

712
00:43:22,232 --> 00:43:26,500
It's better to chill out at the office.

713
00:43:27,266 --> 00:43:28,766
Oh, right.

714
00:43:28,767 --> 00:43:31,200
No need for tiptoeing.

715
00:43:33,999 --> 00:43:35,933
Feels good.

716
00:43:41,566 --> 00:43:45,833
I'll show you what chilling out is.

717
00:43:46,934 --> 00:43:48,434
What?

718
00:43:49,433 --> 00:43:51,366
What's that noise?

719
00:43:57,266 --> 00:43:59,534
Where's his desk?

720
00:44:02,166 --> 00:44:03,566
What?

721
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:11,099
Sir?

722
00:44:11,100 --> 00:44:13,265
What are you doing?

723
00:44:13,265 --> 00:44:15,799
I came to read a book,

724
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:18,565
and moved my desk since it seemed more efficient.

725
00:44:18,566 --> 00:44:20,166
What?

726
00:44:20,166 --> 00:44:21,966
Oh, sir.

727
00:44:21,967 --> 00:44:24,799
How can this be more efficient?

728
00:44:25,532 --> 00:44:27,632
I guess it is.

729
00:44:28,333 --> 00:44:30,999
But why move it yourself? We could've done it tomorrow.

730
00:44:30,999 --> 00:44:34,632
I wanted to do it. What are you doing here on the weekend?

731
00:44:34,632 --> 00:44:38,164
There was nothing to do at home, so I came to the office...

732
00:44:38,164 --> 00:44:41,398
Not to muck around and waste electricity, I hope?

733
00:44:41,399 --> 00:44:42,999
Sir?

734
00:44:42,999 --> 00:44:44,531
Oh, of course not.

735
00:44:44,532 --> 00:44:47,099
I've come to write the promo article.

736
00:44:47,100 --> 00:44:48,798
I did well, right?

737
00:44:48,798 --> 00:44:50,665
Yes. Then get to work.

738
00:44:50,666 --> 00:44:52,433
Yes, sir.

739
00:44:53,220 --> 00:44:54,690

740
00:44:54,699 --> 00:44:55,966
Why are you doing that?

741
00:44:55,967 --> 00:44:58,533
I just want to.

742
00:44:58,533 --> 00:44:59,766
I'll help you. Where...

743
00:44:59,767 --> 00:45:00,799
Where...

744
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:03,665
Your nose must bother you.

745
00:45:03,666 --> 00:45:04,532
Sir?

746
00:45:04,533 --> 00:45:06,966
Since you're so nosy.

747
00:45:06,967 --> 00:45:08,432
Just let me do it.

748
00:45:08,433 --> 00:45:10,131
Don't mind me and go to work.

749
00:45:10,131 --> 00:45:13,964
- But still... 
 - Just mind your own business.

750
00:45:14,899 --> 00:45:17,266
I beg of you.

751
00:45:25,399 --> 00:45:27,898
 Can anyone write an article for me?

752
00:45:27,899 --> 00:45:30,100
 I'll pay.

753
00:45:33,166 --> 00:45:37,700
No, I have my dignity as the chief editor.

754
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:41,666
I'll write it myself.

755
00:45:41,666 --> 00:45:45,600
But I really don't want to!

756
00:45:59,892 --> 00:46:03,260
Si... si... si... sir!

757
00:46:05,232 --> 00:46:06,532
Okay.

758
00:46:13,166 --> 00:46:15,064
Oh, my heart.

759
00:46:15,065 --> 00:46:17,465
What is he doing?

760
00:46:25,766 --> 00:46:27,565
This is great!

761
00:46:27,566 --> 00:46:31,200
- Right, Young Won? 
 - Yes. Totally.

762
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:34,332
Thank you for inviting me.

763
00:46:34,332 --> 00:46:36,600
No problem.

764
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:41,365
The air is so fresh.

765
00:46:41,366 --> 00:46:44,000
It's so therapeutic.

766
00:46:46,366 --> 00:46:48,899
Queen Yeo!

767
00:46:50,467 --> 00:46:52,432
Oh? What are you doing here?

768
00:46:52,433 --> 00:46:53,898
I heard from Photographer Shin.

769
00:46:53,899 --> 00:46:56,299
I should be where Queen Yeo is.

770
00:46:56,300 --> 00:46:58,432
Why are you calling me Queen Yeo?

771
00:46:58,433 --> 00:47:00,432
You are my sovereign overlord.

772
00:47:00,433 --> 00:47:02,165
You saved me from the pits.

773
00:47:02,166 --> 00:47:03,566
Stop.

774
00:47:03,566 --> 00:47:04,433
Did you call him?

775
00:47:04,434 --> 00:47:06,265
Come on, let's go inside.

776
00:47:06,266 --> 00:47:09,064
Queen Yeo, give me your bag. I'll carry it.

777
00:47:09,064 --> 00:47:10,966
Let's go, let's go!

778
00:47:12,266 --> 00:47:13,765
What is he talking about?

779
00:47:13,765 --> 00:47:15,799
Why is he calling you "Queen Yeo"?

780
00:47:15,800 --> 00:47:18,132
Don't worry about it.

781
00:47:18,133 --> 00:47:19,832
Let's go inside.

782
00:47:19,832 --> 00:47:21,365
This is great.

783
00:47:21,967 --> 00:47:25,999
Wow, awesome.

784
00:47:28,532 --> 00:47:32,931
Since you always stayed at your studio, I forgot you were from a rich family.

785
00:47:32,931 --> 00:47:34,299
But now it's really hitting me.

786
00:47:34,300 --> 00:47:35,467
Yes.

787
00:47:35,467 --> 00:47:37,265
Is this your parents' vacation home?

788
00:47:37,265 --> 00:47:38,199
Yes.

789
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:42,067
Did CEO Yoo get this for them?

790
00:47:44,166 --> 00:47:46,299
What? CEO Yoo didn't get this for them?

791
00:47:46,300 --> 00:47:49,265
I heard CEO Yoo is close with your parents.

792
00:47:49,266 --> 00:47:50,766
What's wrong?

793
00:47:50,767 --> 00:47:52,966
I heard CEO Yoo talk about it the other time.

794
00:47:52,966 --> 00:47:54,099
Shut up!

795
00:47:54,100 --> 00:47:57,400
Do I have to hear that name all the way here?

796
00:47:58,700 --> 00:48:00,067
Okay. I won't mention him.

797
00:48:00,067 --> 00:48:02,766
I shouldn't spoil Queen Yeo's mood.

798
00:48:02,767 --> 00:48:04,799
Why? I'm curious, too.

799
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:06,932
Did CEO Yoo get your parents this house?

800
00:48:06,932 --> 00:48:08,632
Oh, yes.

801
00:48:08,633 --> 00:48:12,300
Wow, he really is competent.

802
00:48:12,300 --> 00:48:13,799
How did he find this house?

803
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:15,933
- Amazing. 
 - Editor Na, shut up!

804
00:48:15,934 --> 00:48:19,365
Queen Yeo doesn't want to hear that name.

805
00:48:19,366 --> 00:48:21,131
You shut up, for goodness' sake.

806
00:48:21,131 --> 00:48:22,265
Please? All right?

807
00:48:22,265 --> 00:48:24,365
Let's take a walk around the neighborhood.

808
00:48:24,365 --> 00:48:26,132
Sounds great. Let's go.

809
00:48:26,132 --> 00:48:28,099
I'll quickly go to the bathroom.

810
00:48:28,100 --> 00:48:29,531
Go on ahead.

811
00:48:29,532 --> 00:48:31,032
Okay.

812
00:48:45,666 --> 00:48:47,933
 Thank you for being so thoughtful.

813
00:48:47,934 --> 00:48:49,665
 This was your idea.

814
00:48:49,666 --> 00:48:52,798
 You said let's take her to cheer her up.

815
00:48:52,798 --> 00:48:56,031
 I worried about her but didn't think to try this.

816
00:48:56,032 --> 00:49:01,499
 I feel bad I didn't catch on quickly enough and made her eat with Ja Sung.

817
00:49:01,499 --> 00:49:06,432
 I, too, feel bad about telling you about Young Won and CEO Yoo.

818
00:49:06,433 --> 00:49:10,534
 You told me so I wouldn't make a mistake again.

819
00:49:10,534 --> 00:49:12,932
 If Young Won finds out, all hell will break loose,

820
00:49:12,932 --> 00:49:16,365
 so please keep it a secret from her.

821
00:49:16,366 --> 00:49:20,533
 Of course. Let's do everything to cheer her up.

822
00:49:20,533 --> 00:49:24,266
 Yes. So she won't have time to feel glum.

823
00:49:33,666 --> 00:49:36,699
 They're doing their best to cheer me up.

824
00:49:36,699 --> 00:49:39,000
 I shouldn't be so down.

825
00:49:39,467 --> 00:49:41,600
I should make an effort.

826
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:47,266
I can get over him.

827
00:49:56,633 --> 00:49:58,899
What is it this time?

828
00:50:10,366 --> 00:50:12,898
What are you doing, sir?

829
